March 4 2026.
A new file was added. CstringsMallocOut.c.
This one allocates and frees memory outside the while loops.
The original allocates inside the loops.
This is ok becouse most users wont select r and when they do
they will do very few iterations of the loops.
Allocating the memory inside the loops is easer to read.
Allocating the memory outside is better if r is selected and
and choices are repeated many times.
